  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Keep a Girl in School In Northern Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over 15 million children in Northern Nigeria are out of school due to crisis and poverty out of which 70% of this figure are girls (UNICEF Report 2018). This project plans to build a 5 blocks of classrooms with furnitures and fittings, provide sick bay equipments and first aid, Ventilated Improved Pit Latrines, provide supply of books, literacy support services for girls in Government Junior Secondary Schools in Tarauni Local Government Council in Kano. This project will affect 1950 girls</narrative>
  </description>
